IT HAS BEEN DETERMINED THAT A ""HOT ZONE"" EXISTS 200 FEET","FROM THE CLEARANCE POINT ON THE ENTRANCE OF THE TRACKS IN THE CLASSIFICATION YARD.  NO CAR SHOULD BE","HUMPED INTO THIS HOT ZONE WHEN IT IS OCCUPIED BY ANOTHER CAR.  IT WAS NOTED THAT FOR AN ALARM MESSA","GE TO BE SENT BY PRO YARDS, CARS MUST BE STATIONARY IN THIS HOT ZONE.  BY DESIGN, PRO YARDS CIRCUITR","Y DOES NOT ALWAYS PROTECT AGAINST CARS WHICH MAY FOUL ADJACENT TRACKS.  ONCE THE THIRD AXLE OF A CAR","PASSES OVER THE SWITCH OCCUPANCY CIRCUITRY ON A TRACK, PRO YARDS CONSIDERS THIS CAR AS BEING IN THE","CLEAR ON THE TARGET TRACK.  IF THE CAR STRIKES ANOTHER CAR IN THE HOT ZONE IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE TH","IRD AXLE PASSES OVER THE SWITCH CIRCUIT AND COMES TO A HALT, THERE IS GREAT EXPOSURE TO A CORNERING","INCIDENT AS A RESULT OF A PORTION OF THE CAR FOULING AN ADJACENT TRACK.
